(57, 'Gender, HIV/AIDS and Disabilities', 'The Debre Markos University Gender Office has the following activities:\r\nGiving trainings such as assertiveness, study skill, reproductive health and life skill (campus life) especially for female students together with both governmental and non-governmental organizations.\r\nGiving consultancy services for both students not only in their academic problems but also in other social and family problems.\r\nFinding funds for students who are economically weak.\r\nGiving tutorial classes to female students collaborating with departments and faculties\r\nMainstreaming gender issues in the university.', '', 'upload/new.docx', '2015-06-04 22:01:59', 'public_relation_committee'),
